From: davesimp@cory.EECS.Berkeley.EDU (David Simpson)
Crossposted-To: comp.unix.admin
Subject: software management/installation
Date: 14 Nov 1993 06:53:26 GMT


        I am looking for a software management/installation tool for
use on my home unix system (running Linux).  I don't need any special
features beside the basics of being able to easily install and
de-install software from either independent directors or tar files.
Anything that deals with multiple users checking files out, or NFS
mounting remotely is probably going too far beyond my needs, unless of
course I can still do what I want to do without being bogged down with
too many other details.

Thanks,

David Simpson




